Document: VisualShaderNodeMix
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodemix.rst
Summary: Represents the mix function in shader language, combining two values based on a weight parameter.

Translates to mix(a, b, weight) in the shader language. This node blends two input values (a and b) using a weight parameter that determines the contribution of each value to the final output. The weight parameter typically ranges between 0 and 1, where 0 returns a, 1 returns b, and values in between produce a smooth interpolation.
